// ==========================================================================
// APPLICATION GUIDE — v43
// ==========================================================================
//
// STEP 1 — Import all measures (Power BI Desktop → Make changes to this model)
//   For each measure: New measure → paste DAX → Enter
//   Assign to table: gold_hvac_analytics
//   Total new measures: ~22
//
// STEP 2 — Update Card Callout values
//   C1  HVAC Share %        → Callout: Card: HVAC Share v43
//   C2  HVAC Efficiency     → Callout: Card: HVAC Efficiency v43          ← FIX decimal
//   C3  Avg Insulation      → Callout: Card: Avg Insulation v43
//   C4  Heat Loss           → Callout: Card: Heat Loss v43
//   C5  Retrofit Count      → Callout: Card: Buildings For Retrofit v43   ← FIX integer filter
//   C6  HVAC CO₂            → Callout: Card: HVAC CO2 v43
//   C7  Gas Exposure %      → Callout: Card: Gas Exposure v43             ← FIX blank→0%
//   C8  EPC Compliance      → Callout: Card: EPC Compliance v43           ← FIX blank→0
//
// STEP 3 — Update Reference Labels (English)
//   C1  → Reference label: Card: HVAC Share Label v43
//   C2  → Reference label: Card: HVAC Efficiency Label v43
//   C3  → Reference label: Card: Insulation Label v43
//   C4  → Reference label: Card: Heat Loss Label v43
//   C5  → Reference label: Card: Retrofit Label v43                       ← FIX string filter
//   C6  → Reference label: Card: CO2 Label v43
//   C7  → Reference label: Card: Gas Exposure Label v43
//   C8  → Reference label: Card: EPC Label v43
//
// STEP 4 — Add YoY/MoM to card Tooltips (time intelligence)
//   C1  tooltip → Card: HVAC Share MoM v43
//   C3  tooltip → Card: Insulation YoY v43
//   C4  tooltip → Card: Heat Loss YoY v43
//   C6  tooltip → Card: CO2 YoY v43
//   How: Select card → Format → Tooltips → Values → drag measure
//
// STEP 5 — V1 Chart: absolute kWh (not 100% stacked)
//   Click V1 → Format pane → Y axis → Turn OFF "Stack to 100%"
//   Result: shows actual monthly kWh split (heating dominates in winter)
//   Optional: V1 → Add data field → Y-axis → Heating Prior Year v43
//             Format this series as Line + dashed + color #FF6B35
//
// STEP 6 — Slicer: remove (Blank) option
//   Click Building Name slicer → Filters pane (right) →
//   "Filters on this visual" → building_name → uncheck "Show items with no data"
//   OR: Slicer → Format → Slicer settings → Show "Select all" → ON
//       Then add a filter: building_name is not blank
//
// STEP 7 — V2 Table: rename columns for readability
//   Click V2 → Columns field well → right-click each field → Rename:
//   building_name → "Building"
//   System Type Display v39 → "System"
//   Renovation Priority Icon v39 → "Priority"
//   COP Display v39 → "COP / SCOP"
//   Scope Badge v40 → "Scope"
//   insulation_score → "Insulation"
//   Card: Heat Loss v43 → "Heat Loss"
//   Action Recommendation v39 → "Action"
//
// VALIDATION CHECKLIST (after all steps):
//   [ ] C1: 20–55% for portfolio  |  winter months higher when date filtered
//   [ ] C2: whole number, no decimals  (e.g. "49" not "58.7999...")
//   [ ] C3: label in English (e.g. "EPC D — Below GEG Limit")
//   [ ] C4: value × 12 applied (e.g. "48 kWh/m²·yr" not "4 kWh/m²")
//   [ ] C5: shows integer count  |  reference label: "2 urgent · 1 planned · 3 OK"
//   [ ] C6: label shows "Scope 1: 65% · Scope 2: 35%"
//   [ ] C7: 0% when only HP/VRF selected  |  50% for full portfolio
//   [ ] C8: "3 / 6 buildings" not "—" for full portfolio
//   [ ] V1: Y-axis shows absolute kWh (heating spikes in Jan/Feb/Nov/Dec)
//   [ ] Slicer: no (Blank) row
//   [ ] V2 columns: English headers, all 6 buildings show data
//
// ==========================================================================
